## Aliases Used

### Network Aliases
- `MGMT_NET` → 192.168.99.0/24  
- `TEST_NET` → 192.168.20.0/24  
- `HOME_NET` → 192.168.30.0/24  
- `IOT_NET` → 192.168.40.0/24  
- `SERVERS_NET` → 192.168.60.0/24  
- `SANDBOX_NET` → 192.168.50.0/24  

### Host Aliases
- `SPLUNK_SERVER` → 192.168.60.10  
- `AD_SERVER` → 192.168.60.20  
- `NAS_SERVER` → 192.168.60.30  

### Port Aliases
- `SPLUNK_PORT` → 9997  
- `AD_PORTS` → 53, 88, 135, 389, 445  

---

## Current Security Posture

### Strengths
- VLAN segmentation enforced
- Critical infrastructure isolated
- IoT network restricted
- Sandbox environment contained

### Known Gaps (Planned Improvements)
- MGMT VLAN is overly permissive
- SERVERS VLAN has unrestricted outbound access
- WAN rules use broad "ANY" instead of port restrictions
- No logging on deny rules yet
- No IDS/IPS enabled

---

